{
  "id": "jasmine-effect-001",
  "title": "The Jasmine Effect - Automate; Don't Panic",
  "theme": "magenta",
  "transition": "slide",
  "createdAt": "2026-05-22T00:00:00.000Z",
  "updatedAt": "2026-05-22T00:00:00.000Z",
  "slides": [
    {
      "id": "s1",
      "background": { "type": "gradient", "value": "linear-gradient(135deg, #ff0084 0%, #33001b 100%)" },
      "elements": [
        { "id": "s1e1", "type": "text", "x": 10, "y": 32, "width": 80, "height": 20, "content": "The Jasmine Effect", "fontSize": 62, "fontWeight": "bold", "fontFamily": "Pacifico", "fontColor": "#ff00ff", "textAlign": "center", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.2, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": true, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s1e2", "type": "text", "x": 25, "y": 58, "width": 50, "height": 8, "content": "Automate; Don't Panic.", "fontSize": 26, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Inter", "fontColor": "#ffffff", "textAlign": "center", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 1, "lineHeight": 1.4, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 0.9, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "s2",
      "background": { "type": "gradient", "value": "linear-gradient(160deg, #8b0040 0%, #3d0020 100%)" },
      "elements": [
        { "id": "s2e1", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 4, "width": 70, "height": 10, "content": "Jasmine's Got Your Back", "fontSize": 38, "fontWeight": "bold", "fontFamily": "Pacifico", "fontColor": "#ff69b4", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.2, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s2e2", "type": "text", "x": 42, "y": 18, "width": 55, "height": 75, "content": "&#8226; Jasmine is a lightweight testing framework for testing JavaScript code.\n\n&#8226; It does not depend on any other JavaScript frameworks.\n\n&#8226; It runs in browsers and in Node.js.\n\n&#8226; Clean, obvious syntax for writing tests.\n\n&#8226; Think of it as a detective who catches bugs before they cause trouble.\n   &#9702; Automated, consistent testing\n   &#9702; Catching bugs early\n   &#9702; Improving script quality", "fontSize": 18, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Inter", "fontColor": "#ffffff", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.6, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "s3",
      "background": { "type": "gradient", "value": "linear-gradient(160deg, #8b0040 0%, #3d0020 100%)" },
      "elements": [
        { "id": "s3e1", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 4, "width": 60, "height": 10, "content": "Prototype", "fontSize": 38, "fontWeight": "bold", "fontFamily": "Pacifico", "fontColor": "#ff69b4", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.2, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s3e2", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 18, "width": 52, "height": 75, "content": "Created by <b>Sam Stephenson</b> in 2005 to simplify and improve the process of writing JavaScript for web development.\n\nIt provided various utilities and extensions to the JavaScript language, such as:\n\n&#8226; Extending built-in JavaScript objects like Array, String, and Function.\n\n&#8226; Easier DOM traversal and manipulation.\n\n&#8226; Cross-browser support.", "fontSize": 18, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Inter", "fontColor": "#ffffff", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.6, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "s4",
      "background": { "type": "gradient", "value": "linear-gradient(160deg, #8b0040 0%, #3d0020 100%)" },
      "elements": [
        { "id": "s4e1", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 4, "width": 90, "height": 10, "content": "ServiceNow's Secret Sauce", "fontSize": 38, "fontWeight": "bold", "fontFamily": "Pacifico", "fontColor": "#ff69b4", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.2, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s4e2", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 20, "width": 90, "height": 70, "content": "ServiceNow uses Prototype.js as its scripting foundation.\n\n<b>Class.create()</b> &#8212; Creates classes\n<b>Object.extendsObject()</b> &#8212; Enables inheritance\n<b>.prototype</b> &#8212; Defines methods and properties\n\nExample:\n<code>var Person = Class.create();\nPerson.prototype = {\n  initialize: function(name) { this.name = name; },\n  say: function(msg) { return this.name + ': ' + msg; },\n  type: 'Person'\n};</code>", "fontSize": 17, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Inter", "fontColor": "#ffffff", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.7, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "s5",
      "background": { "type": "gradient", "value": "linear-gradient(160deg, #8b0040 0%, #3d0020 100%)" },
      "elements": [
        { "id": "s5e1", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 4, "width": 60, "height": 10, "content": "Script Includes", "fontSize": 38, "fontWeight": "bold", "fontFamily": "Pacifico", "fontColor": "#ff69b4", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.2, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s5e2", "type": "text", "x": 42, "y": 18, "width": 55, "height": 75, "content": "&#8226; Script Includes are reusable server-side script logic that define a function or class.\n\n&#8226; They execute their script logic only when explicitly called by other scripts.\n\n&#8226; They are a powerful way to write code that can be called from multiple places, making your instance more modular, maintainable, and efficient.", "fontSize": 18, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Inter", "fontColor": "#ffffff", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.7, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "s6",
      "background": { "type": "gradient", "value": "linear-gradient(160deg, #8b0040 0%, #3d0020 100%)" },
      "elements": [
        { "id": "s6e1", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 4, "width": 90, "height": 10, "content": "Script Includes Patterns", "fontSize": 38, "fontWeight": "bold", "fontFamily": "Pacifico", "fontColor": "#ff69b4", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.2, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s6e2", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 18, "width": 43, "height": 75, "content": "<b>Parent Class:</b>\n\nvar ParentSI = Class.create();\nParentSI.prototype = {\n  initialize: function() { ... },\n  parentFunc: function() { ... },\n  funcToBeOverriden: function() { ... },\n  type: 'ParentSI'\n};", "fontSize": 15, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Fira Code", "fontColor": "#e0e0e0", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.6, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "borderWidth": 1, "borderColor": "#555", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 8, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s6e3", "type": "text", "x": 52, "y": 18, "width": 45, "height": 75, "content": "<b>Child Class:</b>\n\nvar ChildSI = Class.create();\nChildSI.prototype = \n  Object.extendsObject(ParentSI, {\n  initialize: function() {\n    ParentSI.prototype\n      .initialize.call(this);\n  },\n  childFunc: function() { ... },\n  type: 'ChildSI'\n});", "fontSize": 15, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Fira Code", "fontColor": "#e0e0e0", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.6, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "borderWidth": 1, "borderColor": "#555", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 8, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "s7",
      "background": { "type": "gradient", "value": "linear-gradient(160deg, #8b0040 0%, #3d0020 100%)" },
      "elements": [
        { "id": "s7e1", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 4, "width": 90, "height": 10, "content": "Suites: describe Your Tests", "fontSize": 38, "fontWeight": "bold", "fontFamily": "Pacifico", "fontColor": "#ff69b4", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.2, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s7e2", "type": "text", "x": 42, "y": 18, "width": 55, "height": 75, "content": "&#8226; The <b>describe</b> function is for <b>grouping related specs;</b> typically, each test file has one at the top level.\n\n&#8226; The string parameter is for naming the collection of specs, and will be concatenated with specs to make a spec's full name.\n   &#9702; This aids in finding specs in a large suite.\n   &#9702; If you name them well, your specs read as full sentences in traditional BDD style.", "fontSize": 18, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Inter", "fontColor": "#ffffff", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.7, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "s8",
      "background": { "type": "gradient", "value": "linear-gradient(160deg, #8b0040 0%, #3d0020 100%)" },
      "elements": [
        { "id": "s8e1", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 4, "width": 40, "height": 10, "content": "Specs", "fontSize": 38, "fontWeight": "bold", "fontFamily": "Pacifico", "fontColor": "#ff69b4", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.2, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s8e2", "type": "text", "x": 42, "y": 18, "width": 55, "height": 75, "content": "&#8226; Specs are defined by calling the global Jasmine function <b>it</b>, which takes a string and a function.\n\n&#8226; The string is the title of the spec and the function is the spec, or test.\n\n&#8226; A spec contains one or more expectations that test the state of the code.\n   &#9702; An expectation is an assertion that is either true or false.\n   &#9702; A spec with all true expectations is a passing spec.\n   &#9702; A spec with one or more false expectations is a failing spec.", "fontSize": 17, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Inter", "fontColor": "#ffffff", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.7, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "s9",
      "background": { "type": "gradient", "value": "linear-gradient(160deg, #8b0040 0%, #3d0020 100%)" },
      "elements": [
        { "id": "s9e1", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 4, "width": 60, "height": 10, "content": "Expectations & Matchers", "fontSize": 36, "fontWeight": "bold", "fontFamily": "Pacifico", "fontColor": "#ff69b4", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.2, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s9e2", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 18, "width": 90, "height": 75, "content": "&#8226; Expectations are built with the function <b>expect</b> which takes a value, called the actual.\n\n&#8226; It is chained with a Matcher function, which takes the expected value.\n\n&#8226; Each matcher implements a boolean comparison between the actual and expected value.\n\n&#8226; It is responsible for reporting to Jasmine if the expectation is true or false.\n\n&#8226; Any matcher can evaluate to a negative assertion by chaining the call to expect with <b>not</b> before calling the matcher.\n\n&#8226; Jasmine has a rich set of matchers included.", "fontSize": 17, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Inter", "fontColor": "#ffffff", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.6, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "s10",
      "background": { "type": "gradient", "value": "linear-gradient(160deg, #8b0040 0%, #3d0020 100%)" },
      "elements": [
        { "id": "s10e1", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 4, "width": 70, "height": 10, "content": "Setup and Teardown", "fontSize": 38, "fontWeight": "bold", "fontFamily": "Pacifico", "fontColor": "#ff69b4", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.2, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s10e2", "type": "text", "x": 42, "y": 18, "width": 55, "height": 78, "content": "&#8226; To help a test suite <b>DRY</b> up duplicated setup and teardown code, Jasmine provides:\n   <b>beforeEach</b>, <b>afterEach</b>,\n   <b>beforeAll</b>, and <b>afterAll</b>\n\n&#8226; <b>beforeEach</b> is called once before each spec in the describe.\n\n&#8226; <b>afterEach</b> is called once after each spec.\n\n&#8226; <b>beforeAll</b> is called only once before all the specs.\n\n&#8226; <b>afterAll</b> is called after all specs finish.\n\n&#8226; beforeAll/afterAll can speed up test suites with expensive setup and teardown.", "fontSize": 16, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Inter", "fontColor": "#ffffff", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.6, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "s11",
      "background": { "type": "gradient", "value": "linear-gradient(160deg, #8b0040 0%, #3d0020 100%)" },
      "elements": [
        { "id": "s11e1", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 4, "width": 70, "height": 10, "content": "Spies", "fontSize": 38, "fontWeight": "bold", "fontFamily": "Pacifico", "fontColor": "#ff69b4", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.2, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s11e2", "type": "text", "x": 42, "y": 18, "width": 55, "height": 78, "content": "&#8226; Jasmine has test double functions called <b>spies</b>.\n\n&#8226; A spy can stub any function and tracks calls to it and all arguments.\n\n&#8226; A spy <b>only exists in the describe or it block in which it is defined</b>, and will be removed after each spec.\n\n&#8226; Special matchers for spies:\n   &#9702; <b>toHaveBeenCalled</b> &#8212; passes if spy was called\n   &#9702; <b>toHaveBeenCalledTimes</b> &#8212; specific call count\n   &#9702; <b>toHaveBeenCalledWith</b> &#8212; argument matching", "fontSize": 17, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Inter", "fontColor": "#ffffff", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.6, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "s12",
      "background": { "type": "gradient", "value": "linear-gradient(135deg, #ff0084 0%, #33001b 100%)" },
      "elements": [
        { "id": "s12e1", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 4, "width": 60, "height": 10, "content": "References", "fontSize": 38, "fontWeight": "bold", "fontFamily": "Pacifico", "fontColor": "#ff69b4", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "middle", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 1.2, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" },
        { "id": "s12e2", "type": "text", "x": 5, "y": 20, "width": 90, "height": 70, "content": "&#8226; http://prototypejs.org/\n&#8226; https://jasmine.github.io/\n&#8226; Objects: Making It A Little Easier...\n&#8226; Script Includes\n&#8226; NOWCommunity Live Stream &#8211; Code Decoded &#8211; Using a Constants script include\n&#8226; Live Coding Happy Hour for 2017-02-10 &#8211; Server Scripts with ATF\n&#8226; Unit testing your Javascript with jasmine\n&#8226; Unlearn Series &#8211; Unit Test Your Script Include Using ATF\n&#8226; Learning Unit Testing with Jasmine", "fontSize": 18, "fontWeight": "normal", "fontFamily": "Inter", "fontColor": "#ffcc00", "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top", "letterSpacing": 0, "lineHeight": 2.0, "textTransform": "none", "textShadow": false, "rotation": 0, "opacity": 1, "locked": false, "zIndex": 1, "backgroundColor": "", "borderWidth": 0, "borderColor": "#ffffff", "borderStyle": "solid", "borderRadius": 0, "shadowEnabled": false, "shadowColor": "rgba(0,0,0,0.3)", "shadowBlur": 10, "shadowX": 0, "shadowY": 4, "link": "" }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
